<div id=3D"AdThrive_Content_9_tablet" class=3D"adthrive-ad   adthrive-conte=
nt adthrive-content-1" style=3D"min-height: 250px;"></div><h1>Case Study: N=
a=C3=AFve Bayes Classifier From Scratch Using Python</h1>
<p>&nbsp;<br>
An existing problem for any major website today is how to handle virulent a=
nd divisive content. Quora wants to tackle this problem to keep its platfor=
m a place where users can feel safe sharing their knowledge with the world.=
</p>
<p><a href=3D"https://www.quora.com/" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D"noopener">Qu=
ora</a>&nbsp;is a platform that empowers people to learn from each other. O=
n Quora, people can ask questions and connect with others who contribute un=
ique insights and quality answers. A key challenge is to weed out insincere=
 questions =E2=80=94 those founded upon false premises, or that intend to m=
ake a statement rather than look for helpful answers.</p>
<p>The goal is to develop a Na=C3=AFve Bayes classification model that iden=
tifies and flags insincere questions.</p>
<p>The dataset can be downloaded from&nbsp;<a href=3D"https://www.kaggle.co=
m/c/quora-insincere-questions-classification/data" target=3D"_blank" rel=3D=
"noopener">here</a>. Once you have downloaded the train and test data, load=
 it and check.</p>
<div style=3D"width: 98%; overflow: auto; padding-left: 10px; padding-botto=
